A man believed to be linked to a spate of dog poisonings on the West Rand in Gauteng was arrested last Wednesday. This after the police received a call that Apcan Security had nabbed a suspect who was in possession of housebreaking equipment. The security company posted on its Facebook account that one of its officers had spotted and confronted the man on the street before informing the police. WATCH: Quick-thinking pit bull owner stops dognapper from stealing beloved pet According to police spokesperson Sergeant Mpho More, the man was found in possession of a product believed to be dog poison. The 43-year-old will appear at the Roodepoort Magistrate's Court soon. Investigations continue, More added.  GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android or iPhone. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 